At the same time as I laser painted the subject I became aware that other officers had arrived and were proximate. As I believed that the proximate officers could mitigate the threat posed by the subject and could subdue him with less violent means than a taser discharge. As such the timely arrival of other officers meant I formed a different appreciation of the incident and changed tactics to a less violent approach. His response was to "freeze" allowing other options to be considered.
